reviews.review_text: Exellent stuff This a  great show!  Still has Pig pen.  Great sounds, thanks Betty and wild set list, thanks Pigpen!
thanks first Big Railroad Blues that I know of was in the acoustic set at the Fillmore East on 9/20/70.
BRB Guitar Solos The solo's on BRB were used on Skull and Roses. The vocals were from some other date.

The Rub! love this song, was so surprised to hear it pop up in this show, my sources say it was only played 12 times! really rocks here. other than that rare song, the rest of the show is amazing! china rider was good, other one also, great second set overall with bertha squeezed in towards the end

super show, really loving this early 71 run!

What Color are Them There Yodels? Excuse me, but did I just hear a rip-snortin' yodeling session to end out Bobby McGhee?

Yes Ernesto, I did.

First "Sing Me Back Home" I love how they're working out the changes to their first live version of "Sing Me Back Home" while Phil is changing a battery. It even sounds like the PA was turned up to catch it.
Let my guitar playin' friend Only thing to be added after the 1st Sing Me Back Home would be Donna heading into 1972.
